{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Strengthen self-defence rights for adults who intervene to protect children",
        "additional_details": "We would like:\r\n- Rebuttable presumption that force used to defend a child was reasonable.\r\n- Immunity from \u201cexcessive force\u201d charges when honestly believing a child was in imminent danger and acting in good faith.\r\n \r\nWe believe that too many hesitate, fearing arrest. We think this could remove that fear and encourage intervention, while keeping force proportionate.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to amend self-defence law to give explicit statutory protection to any adult who reasonably and proportionately intervenes to protect a child from immediate assault, sexual assault, or grooming.",
